Naive Bayes classification¶

Bayes:

$$ P(\ \text{class} = c_i | \text{text}) = \frac{P(\ \text{text} | \text{class} = c_i \ )P(c_i)}{P(\text{text})}$$

Naive:

If $\text{text} = w_1 w_2 \dots w_n$ then

$$P(\ \text{text} | \text{class} = c_i \ ) = P(w_1 | \text{class} = c_i \ )\cdot P(w_2 | \text{class} = c_i \ )\cdot \dots \cdot P(w_n | \text{class} = c_i \ )$$

We have:

$$P(c_i) = \frac{\text{number of documents in the class } c_i}{\text{ number of all documents}}$$$$P(w | \text{class} = c_i) = \frac{\text{number of occurrences of } w \text{ in } c_i}{\text{number of occurrences of all words in } c_i}$$

The second formula will be improved later.

Solution to Exercise 1¶

In [9]:
from collections import Counter
import re
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
import pandas as pd


movies = pd.read_csv('movie_reviews.zip')
train_df, test_df = train_test_split(movies, test_size=0.5, random_state=1)
grouped = train_df.groupby(by='sentiment')['review'].sum()

words = {}
for k in grouped.index:
    words[k] = Counter(re.findall(r"[a-z']+", grouped[k].replace("<br />", " ").lower()))
word_counts = pd.DataFrame(words).fillna(0).astype(int)
word_counts.to_csv("word_counts.csv")

Solution to Exercise 2¶

In [25]:
import re
import numpy as np

lap_wc = wc + 1
word_log_probs = np.log10(lap_wc/lap_wc.sum())
class_log_probs = np.log10(train_df['sentiment'].value_counts()/len(train_df))
all_words = set(lap_wc.index)

def rev_probs(text):
    words = [w for w in re.findall(r"[a-z']+", text.replace("<br />", "").lower()) if w in all_words]
    w = Counter(words)
    log_probs = ((word_log_probs.loc[list(w.keys())])*np.array(list(w.values()))[:, np.newaxis]).sum(axis=0)
    return log_probs  + class_log_probs

Solution to Exercise 3¶

In [48]:
def make_df(txt):

    matches = re.findall(r"""Newsgroup:\ (.*?)\n   # newsgroup name
                         From:\ (.+?)\n            # from 
                         Subject:\ (.+?)\n+        # subject
                         (.+?)\n+(?=\nNewsgroup:)  # body
                         """,
                         txt,
                         flags=(re.M | re.X | re.S))

    df = pd.DataFrame(matches,
                      columns=["newsgroup", "from", "subject", "body"])

    return df

newsgroups = make_df(txt)
